    <note type="biography">
        <p>Author and artist. Grandson of Samuel Butler (1774–1839). Emigrated to New Zealand in 1859; returned to Britain after publishing an account of his time farming in the colony, <hi rend="italic">A first year in Canterbury settlement</hi> (1863). Published books on art, music, literature, and philosophy, including the novels <hi rend="italic">Erewhon</hi> (1872) and <hi rend="italic">The way of all flesh</hi> (1903); published a two-volume life of his grandfather, <hi rend="italic">Life of Samuel Butler, bishop of Lichfield</hi> (1896). Became a critic of Darwinism from the 1870s.</p></note>
